title: Family and friends of missing British hiker 'extremely worried'
description: The family and friends of a British hiker last seen on a Swiss mountain six weeks ago say they are "extremely worried".

title: Woman kidnapped by fake policeman punched her way out of garage cell
description: A woman kidnapped and held captive in a makeshift cell by a man posing as an undercover police officer punched her way to freedom, the FBI has said.

title: Italian prime minister sues Placebo singer for calling her 'fascist, racist'
description: Italy's Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni is reportedly suing the lead singer of Placebo after he called her a "fascist, racist" at a gig last month.

title: Yacht that Princess Diana spent last summer on sinks to bottom of Med
description: A motor yacht used by Princess Diana and her boyfriend Dodi Al-Fayed on their final summer holiday in the South of France before they died in a Paris car crash has sunk.

title: Nose-picking health workers 'more likely to catch COVID'
description: Hospital workers who pick their noses are more likely to catch COVID, a new study suggests.

title: Yeezy sales back to old levels - despite Adidas severing ties with Kanye West
description: Adidas sold €400m (£345m) worth of Kanye West-designed footwear from April to the end of June this year - as much as the same time last year, despite severing ties with the rapper.

title: 'One dead' and 12 injured after man drives car onto pavement and launches stab attack
description: One person has reportedly died and 12 others were injured in South Korea after a man drove a car onto a pavement and rammed pedestrians, before he got out and stabbed people in a shopping centre.

title: Somali sports official suspended after 'untrained runner' competes in games
description: A Somali sports official has been suspended after an apparently untrained female sprinter represented the African country at an international athletics tournament in China.

title: UK reduces staff numbers at Niger embassy following military coup
description: Britain is reducing the number of staff at its embassy in Niger following last week's military coup.

title: Donald Trump to appear in court to face charges over January 6th Capitol riots
description: Donald Trump is due to appear in court to face charges over involvement in the January 6th Capitol riots.
